|WKBDeath Avengement
|CKO---------------------------------------------------------------------

|YKODeath avengement is the process by which a player avenges another
player's recent death, collecting a bounty and restoring the
victim's lost experience.

When you die, you may ask another player to avenge you. The bounty
- experience and coins - scales with the toughness of whatever
killed you: mightier killers pay far better. If the avenger
succeeds, they collect the bounty, and your death penalty (10% of
your experience on hand) is restored to you, unless a resurrection
already refunded it.

The rules of the system:

  |BKB* |GKBFrom the time of death, the avenged has 30 real time minutes to
    find an avenger, and for that avenger to track and kill the target
    mob.

  |BKB* |GKBNeither the avengee or the avenger may log off during that time,
    else that avenge is forever lost.

  |BKB* |GKBAn avenged player can only have one avenger per death.

  |BKB* |GKBAn avenger can only attempt to avenge one player at a time.

  |BKB* |GKBIf the original killing mob is killed, the avengement is cancelled.
    In the case of PKs, if the killing player logs off, the avengement
    is cancelled.


|YKOSee also: |YKBaskavenge, avengeinfo
